The '''Suikerbond''' ("Sugar Union") was a [[trade union]] for European workers in the sugar industry in the [[Dutch East Indies]]. The organization was founded on 14 March 1907 in [[Surabaya]], as the ''Bond van Geëmployeerden in de Suikerindustrie in Nederlandsch-Indië'' ("Union of those employed in the sugar industry in the Netherlands Indies").<ref>{{cite book|last=Mandere|first=Henri Charles Glaude Jacob|title=De Javasuikerindustrie in heden en verleden: gezien in het bijzonder in hare sociaal-economische beteeknis|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=8hLbAAAAMAAJ|year=1928|publisher=Bureau Industria|language=Dutch|page=85}}</ref>One of the two strongest unions for Europeans,<ref>{{cite book|last=Bosma|first=Ulbe|title=The Sugar Plantation in India and Indonesia: Industrial Production, 1770–2010|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=DZuyAAAAQBAJ&pg=PT207|year=2013|publisher=Cambridge UP|isbn=9781107435308|page=207}}</ref> in the early 1920s, during a wave of strikes by factory workers (many of whom were organized in Communist trade unions), the Suikerbond had been "bought off" by the sugar industry which had raised wages for European workers.<ref name="Ingleson2014">{{cite book|last=Ingleson|first=John|title=Workers, Unions and Politics: Indonesia in the 1920s and 1930s|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=ygPbAgAAQBAJ&pg=PA69|year=2014|publisher=BRILL|isbn=9789004264762|pages=69–70}}</ref> In 1921 the organization founded its own newspaper, ''[[De Indische Courant]]'', which was run by the union's president, W. Burger, and appears in two editions on the island of [[Java]];<ref>{{cite book|last=Maters|first=Mirjam|title=Van zachte wenk tot harde hand: persvrijheid en persbreidel in Nederlands-Indië, 1906-1942|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=hLsHBs4eu48C&pg=PA145|year=1998|publisher=Uitgeverij Verloren|isbn=9789065505965|page=145}}</ref> initially leaning social-democratic, under pressure from union members a more conservative editor in chief was installed.<ref>{{cite book|last=Vogel|first=Jaap|title=De opkomst van het Indocentrische geschiedbeeld: leven en werken van B.J.O. Schrieke en J.C. van Leur|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=tpR28fFbOM8C&pg=RA1-PA190|year=1992|publisher=Uitgeverij Verloren|isbn=9789065504067|page=190}}</ref> By 1922 the organization numbered over 3800 members and had a strike fund of a half a million guilders.<ref>{{cite book|last1=Bosma|first1=Ulbe|last2=Raben|first2=Remco|title=Being "Dutch" in the Indies: A History of Creolisation and Empire, 1500-1920|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=47wCTCJX9X4C&pg=PA395|year=2008|publisher=NUS Press|isbn=9789971693732|page=395}}</ref>

